<subSubSection id="C3776556ED013865FF78FAFFFD3CFAAC" pageId="592" pageNumber="593" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED013865FF78FAFFFD3CFAAC" blockId="592.[136,778,1329,2070]" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED013865FF78FAFFFEFFFA8A" bold="true" box="[189,314,1329,1355]" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific namerefers tothe presence of the paired bullae on the ventral surface of the anal somite.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED013867FF78FABBFBE5FA70" lastPageId="594" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="592" pageNumber="593" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED013865FF78FABBFE83F813" blockId="592.[136,778,1329,2070]" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED013865FF78FABBFE05FA4E" bold="true" box="[189,448,1397,1423]" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FDD8FABBFD56FA51" box="[541,659,1397,1424]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398A</figureCitation>
) elongate, cylindrical, curved dorsally: bodylength 2.06 mm. Prosome unsegmented, narrowing anteriorly and posteriorly from maximum width in mid-region (415 μm wide); cephalosome not demarcated from metasomal region, bearing paired tubercles (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FDC9F9D1FD44F9FB" box="[524,641,1567,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398E</figureCitation>
) on ventral surface located lateral to oral region. Anterior region of prosome, from rostrum to leg 4, occupying about 30% of prosome length; region posterior to insertion of leg 4 forming brood pouch. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FDFBF969FD76F903" box="[574,691,1703,1730]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398B</figureCitation>
) small, consistingof genitalsomiteand 4 abdominalsomites, 137 μm long, curved ventrally. Anal somite (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FD91F925FD0DF8C7" box="[596,712,1771,1798]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398C</figureCitation>
) with paired trilobate swellings (bullae) on ventral surface (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FD19F8C3FF0FF88B" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398D</figureCitation>
), surface of bullae ornamented with spinules, anal somitewithscattered setules. Caudal ramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FDB7F89CFCC4F8AD" box="[626,769,1874,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398C, D</figureCitation>
) small, 18×14 μm, much shorter than anal somite, directed laterally: armed with 6 naked setae and ornamented with scattered setules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED013865FF78F814FC2CF99A" blockId="592.[136,778,1329,2070]" lastBlockId="592.[810,1452,1329,2070]" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FEF6F814FE62F835" box="[307,423,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398F</figureCitation>
) 43×39 μm, tapering towards rounded distal margin, surface covered with setules. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FC68FAFFFBE5FA8A" box="[941,1056,1329,1355]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398G</figureCitation>
) short (about 52 μmlong), strongly tapering, incompletely 5-segmented; first segment with 2 setae; setae on other segments not distinguishable from setules. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FC3AFA59FBBEFA73" box="[1023,1147,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398H</figureCitation>
) stout, 3-segmentedwith short coxa; basis as long as wide, unarmed, broadened proximally; unsegmented endopod about 1.8 times longer than wide (25×14 μ); armed with 4 setae (
<quantity id="4C959B38ED013865FAC8FA30FAFDF9D6" box="[1293,1336,1533,1560]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="592" pageNumber="593" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
middle, 1 subdistal, and 2 distal) plusterminal claw 0.7 times as long as endopod.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED013865FC9AF9ADFC4AF813" blockId="592.[810,1452,1329,2070]" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
Labrum missing. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FB6BF9ADFAD9F9BF" box="[1198,1308,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398I</figureCitation>
) with coxal gnathobase bearing pectinate medial margin; palp consistingof well-defined basis, exopod and endopod; armedwith 1 setaon basis, 4 pinnate setaeon exopod, 1 broad, naked seta on first endopodal segment and 4 setae on second. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FBFFF8C3FB69F8E9" box="[1082,1196,1805,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398J</figureCitation>
) represented by lobe bearing 6 subequal, pinnate setae. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FAEEF8FEFA61F88B" box="[1323,1444,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398K</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, armed with 6 setae (3 medial and 3 on distal margin). Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FBACF8BAFB1BF84F" box="[1129,1246,1908,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 398L</figureCitation>
) small, obscurely 2-segmented, armed with 1 small seta on tip of second segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED013867FC9AF814FD62F900" blockId="592.[810,1452,1329,2070]" lastBlockId="594.[136,778,1431,1730]" lastPageId="594" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">
Legs 1–4 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED013865FC1EF814FBF9F835" box="[987,1084,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURE 399" captionStartId="594.[136,245,1329,1355]" captionTargetBox="[165,1424,207,1256]" captionTargetId="figure-19@594.[136,1451,184,1290]" captionTargetPageId="594" captionText="FIGURE 399. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, leg 1; B, leg 2; C, leg 3; D, leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592114/files/figure.png" pageId="592" pageNumber="593">Fig. 399</figureCitation>
A-D) broad, biramous, setulose, with 2-segmented rami and unsegmented or indistinctly 2-segmented protopod; coxa lacking inner seta. Outer seta on basis lacking in leg 1, but present in legs 2–4. Basis of leg 1 bearing small inner distal seta. First exopodal segment of legs 1–4 bearing broad, bifurcate process at outer distalcorner (outer branch of each process shorter and tipped with 1 to 4 small denticles). All setae on legs 1–4 short. Inner setaon first endopodal segment of legs 1–4 weakly pinnate; all other setae naked and usually blunt. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED003864FF4DF8BDFEEFF835" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="593" pageNumber="594" startId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" targetPageId="593">
