<emphasis id="B919EACFED003864FD97F8BAFD6EF84F" bold="true" box="[594,683,1908,1934]" pageId="593" pageNumber="594">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF126655ED033867FF4DFAFFFA4BFA8D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592114" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592114" box="[136,1422,1329,1356]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592114/files/figure.png" pageId="594" pageNumber="595" startId="594.[136,245,1329,1355]" targetBox="[165,1424,207,1256]" targetPageId="594">
