<figureCitation id="13562A58ED033867FED1F876FE4CF813" box="[276,393,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 398" captionStartId="593.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[201,1345,213,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-18@593.[196,1391,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="593" captionText="FIGURE 398. Campodelphys bullatus sp. nov., female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, right; C, anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal; D, distal part of anal somite, right; E, ventral tubercle of cephalosome; F, rostrum; G, antennule; H, antenna; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla; L, maxilliped. Scale bars: A, 0.2 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–H, 0.02 mm; I–L, 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592112" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592112/files/figure.png" pageId="594" pageNumber="595">Fig. 398B</figureCitation>
) represented by 2 small setae on posteroventral margin of prosome, near base of free urosome.
</paragraph>
